INSERT INTO contract_templates (contract_type, jurisdiction, version, title, preamble, recitals, clauses, signature_block, placeholders, is_active, metadata) VALUES (
  'safe_note',
  'us_california',
  2,
  'Simple Agreement for Future Equity (SAFE) - Valuation Cap and Discount (California)',
  'This Simple Agreement for Future Equity (this "SAFE" or this "Agreement") is entered into and effective as of {{effective_date}} (the "Effective Date") by and between {{party_a_company}}, a California {{entity_type}} with its principal place of business at {{party_a_address}} (the "Company"), and {{party_b_name}}, with an address at {{party_b_address}} (the "Investor").',
  'WHEREAS, the Company desires to raise funds for its business and the Investor desires to provide funds to the Company on the terms set forth herein in exchange for the right to receive equity of the Company upon the occurrence of certain events;

WHEREAS, this SAFE is modeled after the Y Combinator Simple Agreement for Future Equity and is intended to provide standardized, founder-friendly terms for early-stage investment;

WHEREAS, the offer and sale of this SAFE is intended to be exempt from the registration requirements of the Securities Act of 1933, as amended (the "Securities Act"), pursuant to Section 4(a)(2) and/or Rule 506 of Regulation D promulgated thereunder, and exempt from the qualification requirements of the California Corporate Securities Law of 1968 pursuant to California Corporations Code Section 25102(f);

WHEREAS, the parties intend that this SAFE constitutes a binding agreement under applicable law, including the laws of the State of California.

NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants and promises herein and other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which are acknowledged, the parties agree as follows:',
  '[{"id":"definitions","title":"1. DEFINITIONS","content":"1.1 \"Capital Stock\" means the shares of the Company''s capital stock, including any series of preferred stock and common stock, and any other equity securities of the Company.\n\n1.2 \"Equity Financing\" means a bona fide transaction or series of related transactions in which the Company issues and sells shares of its preferred stock (or other equity securities that are substantially similar) for the primary purpose of raising capital, with aggregate gross proceeds to the Company of at least {{qualifying_round_threshold}} (the \"Qualified Financing Threshold\"), excluding (a) issuances pursuant to employee equity incentive plans, (b) issuances upon conversion or exercise of outstanding convertible securities, and (c) issuances in connection with acquisitions, strategic transactions, or equipment/credit financings not principally for equity capital-raising.\n\n1.3 \"Liquidity Event\" means (a) a Change of Control of the Company, or (b) the sale, lease, transfer, exclusive license, or other disposition of all or substantially all of the Company''s assets, in each case in a single transaction or series of related transactions.\n\n1.4 \"Change of Control\" means (a) a merger, consolidation, or other reorganization of the Company after which the holders of the Company''s voting securities immediately prior to such transaction do not hold a majority of the voting power of the surviving or acquiring entity, or (b) any person or group becomes the beneficial owner of a majority of the voting power of the Company.\n\n1.5 \"Dissolution Event\" means (a) the voluntary termination of operations and winding up of the Company, (b) a general assignment for the benefit of the Company''s creditors, or (c) any other liquidation, dissolution, or winding up of the Company (other than a Liquidity Event), whether voluntary or involuntary.\n\n1.6 \"Purchase Amount\" means {{investment_amount}}.\n\n1.7 \"Valuation Cap\" means {{valuation_cap}}.\n\n1.8 \"Discount Rate\" means {{discount_rate}}%.\n\n1.9 \"Safe Securities\" means the securities issued to the Investor upon conversion or settlement of this SAFE pursuant to this Agreement.\n\n1.10 \"Company Capitalization\" means, as of immediately prior to the applicable conversion event, the sum, determined on a fully-diluted, as-converted basis, of: (a) all shares of Capital Stock issued and outstanding, (b) all shares of Capital Stock issuable upon conversion or exercise of all outstanding convertible securities (including this SAFE and all other SAFEs, convertible notes, and similar instruments), (c) all shares of Capital Stock reserved and available for issuance under any equity incentive or stock option plans, (d) all shares of Capital Stock issuable upon exercise of outstanding warrants, and (e) any shares of Capital Stock authorized and reserved for issuance by the Company''s board of directors, as determined in good faith by the Company''s board of directors consistent with customary venture financing practice.\n\n1.11 \"California Securities Law\" means the California Corporate Securities Law of 1968, as amended, California Corporations Code Section 25000 et seq.\n\n1.12 \"CUTSA\" means the California Uniform Trade Secrets Act, California Civil Code Section 3426 et seq.","type":"standard","order":1},{"id":"investment_amount","title":"2. PURCHASE AMOUNT; ISSUANCE","content":"2.1 Purchase. In consideration for the rights described in this SAFE, the Investor hereby agrees to pay the Company, and the Company hereby acknowledges receipt (or will receive receipt within five (5) business days of the Effective Date) of, the Purchase Amount of {{investment_amount}}.\n\n2.2 Form of Payment. Payment will be made by wire transfer, ACH, check, or other means acceptable to the Company to an account designated by the Company in writing.\n\n2.3 No Interest; No Maturity Date. This SAFE (a) does not bear interest, (b) has no maturity date, and (c) is not a debt instrument. The Investor is entitled to receive Safe Securities or other consideration only in accordance with the express terms of this Agreement.\n\n2.4 Use of Proceeds. The Company may use the Purchase Amount for general corporate purposes, including working capital, research and development, sales and marketing, and other business operations, subject to applicable law and any fiduciary duties owed by the Company''s directors and officers.\n\n2.5 Non-Refundable. Except as otherwise expressly provided herein, the Purchase Amount is non-refundable and the Investor shall not be entitled to a return of any portion thereof.","type":"standard","order":2},{"id":"conversion_equity_financing","title":"3. CONVERSION UPON EQUITY FINANCING","content":"3.1 Automatic Conversion. Upon the closing of the first Equity Financing, this SAFE will automatically convert into the number of shares (or other equity securities) of the same series and class issued in such Equity Financing (the \"Financing Securities\") equal to the Purchase Amount divided by the applicable \"SAFE Price\" determined under Section 3.2, without any further action by the Investor.\n\n3.2 SAFE Price. The \"SAFE Price\" per share (or per unit of the Financing Securities) will be the lower of:\n\n(a) the \"Cap Price,\" calculated as the Valuation Cap divided by the Company Capitalization; and\n\n(b) the \"Discount Price,\" calculated as the price per share paid by investors purchasing the Financing Securities in the Equity Financing, multiplied by (1 - Discount Rate).\n\nIf the Equity Financing involves multiple closings, the SAFE Price shall be determined based on the terms of the initial closing. If the Equity Financing includes units or securities with complex pricing (such as bundled warrants or multiple classes), the Company will determine in good faith an equivalent per-share price for purposes of this Section 3.\n\n3.3 Anti-Dilution Protection. The Conversion Price shall be subject to proportional adjustment for stock splits, stock dividends, combinations, recapitalizations, and similar events affecting the Company''s capital structure.\n\n3.4 Fractional Shares. No fractional shares will be issued upon conversion. In lieu of any fractional share, the Company will pay cash equal to such fraction multiplied by the SAFE Price, unless payment of such cash is prohibited by the Equity Financing documents, in which case any fractional share shall be rounded down to the nearest whole share.\n\n3.5 Charter and Other Amendments. In connection with an Equity Financing, the Company may amend its certificate of incorporation, bylaws, or other governing documents to authorize and issue the Financing Securities and take other actions reasonably necessary to effect the conversion of this SAFE, provided such actions do not disproportionately and adversely affect the Investor relative to other holders of substantially similar SAFEs or convertible instruments converting in the same Equity Financing.\n\n3.6 Transaction Documents. As a condition to receiving Financing Securities, the Investor agrees to execute and deliver the definitive transaction documents for the Equity Financing that are generally applicable to investors receiving the same series of Financing Securities (including, without limitation, stock purchase agreements, voting agreements, right of first refusal and co-sale agreements, and investor rights agreements); provided, however, that such documents will not require the Investor to (a) make any additional cash investment beyond the Purchase Amount (except as may be required solely by operation of preemptive or pro rata rights expressly granted under this SAFE), (b) provide any personal guarantee, or (c) be subject to non-compete obligations (which are generally unenforceable under California Business and Professions Code Section 16600).\n\n3.7 Conversion Mechanics. Upon conversion, the Company shall issue a stock certificate or book-entry statement evidencing the Safe Securities to the Investor within thirty (30) days of conversion, update its capitalization table and stock ledger, and take all other actions necessary to effectuate such conversion.","type":"negotiable","order":3},{"id":"liquidity_event","title":"4. LIQUIDITY EVENT","content":"4.1 Treatment at Liquidity Event. If a Liquidity Event occurs prior to the conversion of this SAFE pursuant to Section 3, then at the closing of such Liquidity Event the Investor will be entitled, at the Investor''s election (to be made no later than five (5) business days prior to the closing of the Liquidity Event), to receive either:\n\n(a) \"Cash-Out Amount\": Cash or other consideration equal to the Purchase Amount; or\n\n(b) \"Conversion Amount\": The number of shares of common stock (or the most junior class of equity securities, if different) equal to the Purchase Amount divided by the Liquidity Price, and to participate in the distribution of proceeds from the Liquidity Event on the same terms as other holders of such common stock.\n\n4.2 Liquidity Price. The \"Liquidity Price\" will be the lower of:\n\n(a) the Cap Price (Valuation Cap divided by Company Capitalization); and\n\n(b) the price per share implied by the Liquidity Event consideration for the Company''s common stock, multiplied by (1 - Discount Rate), as determined in good faith by the Company''s board of directors.\n\n4.3 Distribution Waterfall and Seniority. Amounts payable under this Section 4 shall be paid:\n\n(a) After payment of all secured creditors;\n(b) After payment of all amounts owed to senior debt holders;\n(c) Pari passu with other SAFE holders and convertible note holders of similar priority;\n(d) Before any distributions to holders of common stock or junior preferred stock.\n\nIf the total consideration available for payment to holders of SAFEs and other instruments of similar priority is insufficient to pay all such holders in full, the Company will pay such holders pro rata based on their respective Purchase Amounts.\n\n4.4 Form of Consideration. The consideration may be cash, securities, or other property, mirroring the form paid to other equity holders in the Liquidity Event (subject to the election in Section 4.1 and applicable law).\n\n4.5 Investor Election Default. If the Investor fails to make an election under Section 4.1(a) or (b), the Investor shall be deemed to have elected the Cash-Out Amount under Section 4.1(a).","type":"negotiable","order":4},{"id":"dissolution_event","title":"5. DISSOLUTION EVENT","content":"5.1 Payment upon Dissolution. If a Dissolution Event occurs prior to the conversion of this SAFE pursuant to Section 3, the Investor will be entitled to receive, from the assets legally available for distribution to stockholders after payment of all creditors and satisfaction of all liquidation preferences of outstanding preferred stock, a distribution amount equal to the Purchase Amount.\n\n5.2 Distribution Waterfall. Upon a Dissolution Event, the Company''s assets shall be distributed in the following order of priority:\n\n(a) First, to creditors (including employees owed wages) in accordance with applicable law;\n(b) Second, to holders of any outstanding preferred stock in accordance with their liquidation preferences;\n(c) Third, to holders of SAFEs and convertible instruments on a pari passu basis, pro rata based on Purchase Amounts;\n(d) Finally, to holders of common stock.\n\n5.3 Pro Rata if Insufficient Assets. If the Company''s assets legally available for distribution are insufficient to pay the amounts owed to all holders of SAFEs and other instruments of similar priority in full, the Company will pay such holders pro rata in proportion to their respective Purchase Amounts or principal-equivalent amounts.\n\n5.4 No Further Rights. Upon payment (if any) under this Section 5, this SAFE shall terminate and the Investor will have no further rights under this SAFE with respect to the Company.","type":"standard","order":5},{"id":"valuation_cap_discount","title":"6. VALUATION CAP AND DISCOUNT MECHANICS","content":"6.1 Valuation Cap. The Valuation Cap for purposes of this SAFE is {{valuation_cap}}. The Valuation Cap represents the maximum effective pre-money valuation at which the SAFE will convert, providing the Investor with downside protection in the event the Company achieves a higher valuation in a subsequent Equity Financing.\n\n6.2 Discount Rate. The Discount Rate for purposes of this SAFE is {{discount_rate}}%. The Discount provides the Investor with a reduction from the price per share paid by investors in the Equity Financing, in recognition of the Investor''s early-stage investment risk.\n\n6.3 Better of Cap or Discount. In calculating the SAFE Price, the Investor will receive whichever of the Cap Price or Discount Price results in more shares (i.e., the lower price per share), not both.\n\n6.4 Example Calculation. [For illustration only] If the Valuation Cap is $5,000,000, Company Capitalization is 10,000,000 shares, the Discount Rate is 20%, and the Equity Financing price is $1.00 per share: Cap Price = $5,000,000 / 10,000,000 = $0.50; Discount Price = $1.00 x (1 - 0.20) = $0.80; SAFE Price = $0.50 (lower of the two).","type":"negotiable","order":6},{"id":"mfn_clause","title":"7. MOST FAVORED NATION (MFN) PROVISION","content":"7.1 MFN Right. If, prior to the conversion or termination of this SAFE, the Company issues any subsequent SAFE, convertible note, or similar convertible security (a \"Subsequent Convertible Security\") that contains terms more favorable to the investor thereunder than the terms of this SAFE, including without limitation: (a) a higher Valuation Cap (which would be more favorable to the Investor if this SAFE had such higher cap); (b) a higher Discount Rate; (c) more favorable conversion mechanics; (d) information rights or other rights not provided herein; or (e) other material economic or protective terms, then the Investor shall have the right, upon written notice to the Company within thirty (30) days after receiving notice of such issuance, to amend this SAFE to include such more favorable terms.\n\n7.2 Notice Requirement. The Company shall provide the Investor with written notice of any Subsequent Convertible Security issuance within ten (10) business days of such issuance, including a summary of the material terms thereof.\n\n7.3 Amendment Mechanics. If the Investor elects to exercise MFN rights, the parties shall execute an amendment to this SAFE incorporating the more favorable terms, effective as of the date of issuance of the Subsequent Convertible Security.\n\n7.4 Exceptions. The MFN right shall not apply to: (a) issuances to employees, directors, or consultants under equity incentive plans; (b) issuances in connection with strategic transactions approved by the Company''s board of directors; or (c) amendments to existing convertible securities that do not involve new capital.","type":"negotiable","order":7},{"id":"pro_rata_rights","title":"8. PRO RATA RIGHTS","content":"8.1 Grant of Pro Rata Right. Subject to the limitations in this Section 8, the Company grants the Investor a pro rata right to purchase, at the same price and on substantially the same terms as offered to other investors, additional securities issued by the Company in an Equity Financing in order to maintain the Investor''s percentage ownership in the Company on a fully-diluted basis immediately prior to such Equity Financing (the \"Pro Rata Right\").\n\n8.2 Calculation. The Investor''s pro rata entitlement will be calculated in good faith by the Company based on Company Capitalization immediately prior to the closing of the Equity Financing, taking into account the conversion of this SAFE and other SAFEs/convertible instruments participating in the Equity Financing.\n\n8.3 Notice and Election. The Company will provide the Investor written notice (email to {{party_b_email}} is sufficient) describing the Equity Financing, including the material terms thereof, the Investor''s pro rata allocation, and the deadline to elect participation. The election deadline will be no less than {{notice_period}} days after the notice is sent, unless the Equity Financing schedule reasonably requires a shorter period (but in no event less than five (5) days).\n\n8.4 Limitations and Exclusions. The Pro Rata Right does not apply to: (a) issuances under employee, director, or consultant equity incentive plans approved by the Company''s board of directors; (b) securities issued in connection with equipment financings, bank loans, lines of credit, or other debt financings not principally for equity capital-raising; (c) securities issued as consideration in acquisitions, mergers, or strategic transactions approved by the Company''s board of directors; (d) securities issued upon conversion of convertible securities; or (e) other excluded issuances approved in good faith by the Company''s board of directors.\n\n8.5 Transferability. The Pro Rata Right is personal to the Investor and non-transferable except in connection with a permitted transfer of this SAFE pursuant to Section 11.2.","type":"optional","order":8},{"id":"information_rights","title":"9. INFORMATION RIGHTS","content":"9.1 Basic Information Rights. Until the earlier of (a) the conversion of this SAFE into Safe Securities, (b) the termination of this SAFE, or (c) such time as this SAFE is no longer outstanding, the Company shall provide the Investor with:\n\n(a) Annual financial statements (balance sheet, income statement, and statement of cash flows), prepared in accordance with GAAP or on a consistent basis, within one hundred twenty (120) days after the end of each fiscal year;\n\n(b) Prompt notice (and in any event within ten (10) business days) of any Equity Financing, Liquidity Event, or Dissolution Event;\n\n(c) Upon reasonable request, access to information reasonably necessary for the Investor to comply with tax reporting requirements.\n\n9.2 Confidentiality. The Investor agrees to maintain the confidentiality of all non-public information received from the Company pursuant to this Section 9 and to use such information solely for purposes of monitoring the Investor''s investment in the Company.\n\n9.3 Termination of Information Rights. The information rights under this Section 9 shall terminate upon conversion of this SAFE into Safe Securities, at which time the Investor''s information rights (if any) shall be governed by the Equity Financing documents.","type":"standard","order":9},{"id":"company_representations","title":"10. COMPANY REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES","content":"The Company represents and warrants to the Investor as of the Effective Date that:\n\n10.1 Organization and Authority. The Company is duly organized, validly existing, and in good standing under the laws of the State of California and has the requisite corporate power and authority to enter into this SAFE and perform its obligations hereunder.\n\n10.2 Authorization. The execution, delivery, and performance of this SAFE have been duly authorized by all necessary corporate action, including approval by the Company''s board of directors, and this SAFE constitutes a legal, valid, and binding obligation of the Company enforceable against the Company in accordance with its terms, subject to bankruptcy, insolvency, fraudulent transfer, reorganization, moratorium, and similar laws affecting creditors'' rights and general principles of equity.\n\n10.3 No Conflict. The execution, delivery, and performance of this SAFE do not (a) violate the Company''s articles of incorporation, bylaws, or other governing documents, (b) to the Company''s knowledge, violate any material agreement, contract, or instrument binding on the Company, or (c) violate any applicable law, rule, or regulation.\n\n10.4 Securities Law Compliance. The offer and sale of this SAFE is intended to be exempt from the registration requirements of the Securities Act pursuant to Section 4(a)(2) and/or Rule 506 of Regulation D, and exempt from the qualification requirements of the California Securities Law pursuant to California Corporations Code Section 25102(f). The Company will issue Safe Securities, if and when issued, in compliance with applicable federal and state securities laws, including applicable exemptions from registration.\n\n10.5 No Broker. The Company has not engaged any broker, finder, or investment banker entitled to any brokerage, finder''s, or other fee or commission payable by the Investor in connection with the transactions contemplated by this SAFE.\n\n10.6 Capitalization. The Company has provided or will provide the Investor with a capitalization table that accurately reflects the Company''s capital structure as of the Effective Date.","type":"standard","order":10},{"id":"investor_representations","title":"11. INVESTOR REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES","content":"The Investor represents and warrants to the Company as of the Effective Date that:\n\n11.1 Authority. The Investor has full power and authority to enter into this SAFE. This SAFE constitutes a legal, valid, and binding obligation of the Investor enforceable against the Investor in accordance with its terms, subject to bankruptcy, insolvency, and similar laws affecting creditors'' rights and equitable principles.\n\n11.2 Investment Purpose. The Investor is acquiring this SAFE for the Investor''s own account for investment purposes and not with a view to, or for sale in connection with, any distribution thereof in violation of applicable securities laws.\n\n11.3 Sophistication; Risk. The Investor (a) has such knowledge and experience in financial and business matters as to be capable of evaluating the merits and risks of an investment in the Company, (b) has had the opportunity to ask questions of and receive answers from the Company concerning the Company and this investment, (c) has received and reviewed all information the Investor deems necessary to make an informed investment decision, and (d) understands that the investment is speculative and involves a high degree of risk, including the risk of total loss of the entire Purchase Amount.\n\n11.4 Accredited Investor Status. The Investor is an \"accredited investor\" as defined in Rule 501(a) of Regulation D promulgated under the Securities Act, and can bear the economic risk of investment in this SAFE, including total loss. [If applicable, the Investor has completed and provided to the Company an accredited investor questionnaire.]\n\n11.5 No Governmental Approvals. No consent, approval, order, or authorization of, or registration, qualification, designation, declaration, or filing with, any federal, state, or local governmental authority is required on the part of the Investor in connection with the consummation of the transactions contemplated hereby, except as may be required under applicable securities laws.\n\n11.6 Residence. The Investor''s address set forth in this SAFE is the Investor''s principal residence (if an individual) or principal place of business (if an entity), as applicable, and the Investor is a bona fide resident of such jurisdiction.\n\n11.7 No Public Solicitation. The Investor was not induced to invest in this SAFE by any form of general solicitation or general advertising.","type":"standard","order":11},{"id":"transfer_and_assignment","title":"12. TRANSFER; ASSIGNMENT","content":"12.1 Company Assignment. The Company may not assign this SAFE or any of its rights or obligations hereunder without the prior written consent of the Investor, except that the Company may assign this SAFE without consent in connection with a merger, consolidation, reorganization, or sale of all or substantially all of the Company''s assets (including in a Liquidity Event), provided that the successor entity assumes in writing all of the Company''s obligations hereunder.\n\n12.2 Investor Transfer. The Investor may not transfer or assign this SAFE, in whole or in part, without the Company''s prior written consent; provided, however, that the Investor may transfer this SAFE without the Company''s consent to:\n\n(a) an affiliate of the Investor (meaning an entity that controls, is controlled by, or is under common control with the Investor);\n(b) a trust for the benefit of the Investor or the Investor''s immediate family members;\n(c) in the case of an individual, to the Investor''s spouse, children, or lineal descendants, or to a trust primarily for the benefit of the Investor or such family members;\n(d) in the case of an entity, to a successor in connection with a reorganization, merger, or similar transaction;\n\nin each case, subject to the transferee agreeing in writing to be bound by all terms of this SAFE and compliance with applicable securities laws.\n\n12.3 Securities Law Compliance. Any transfer must be made in compliance with applicable federal and state securities laws (including any applicable exemptions from registration or qualification) and may be subject to restrictions on transfer set forth in the Company''s governing documents and/or in any financing documents. The Company may require, as a condition to any transfer, an opinion of counsel satisfactory to the Company that such transfer complies with applicable securities laws.\n\n12.4 Legend. This SAFE and any Safe Securities issued upon conversion hereof shall bear a restrictive legend substantially in the form required by applicable securities laws and the Company''s governing documents.","type":"negotiable","order":12},{"id":"miscellaneous","title":"13. MISCELLANEOUS","content":"13.1 Notices. All notices and other communications will be in writing and will be deemed given (a) when delivered personally, (b) when sent by confirmed email (with read receipt or confirmation of delivery), (c) one (1) business day after being sent by a nationally recognized overnight courier (such as FedEx or UPS), or (d) three (3) business days after being mailed by certified or registered mail, return receipt requested, in each case to the addresses/emails set forth below (or to such other address as a party may designate by written notice):\n\nIf to the Company:\n{{party_a_company}}\n{{party_a_address}}\nEmail: {{party_a_email}}\nAttn: {{party_a_name}}, {{party_a_title}}\n\nIf to the Investor:\n{{party_b_name}}\n{{party_b_address}}\nEmail: {{party_b_email}}\n\n13.2 Governing Law. This SAFE and all claims arising out of or relating to this SAFE will be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of California, without giving effect to any choice-of-law or conflict-of-law rules that would result in the application of the laws of another jurisdiction.\n\n13.3 Amendments and Waivers. Any term of this SAFE may be amended, and any provision may be waived, only with the written consent of the Company and the Investor. Any waiver is effective only if in writing and signed by the waiving party and only for the specific instance for which it is given.\n\n13.4 Severability. If any provision of this SAFE is held to be invalid, illegal, or unenforceable by a court of competent jurisdiction, the remaining provisions will remain in full force and effect, and the invalid, illegal, or unenforceable provision will be modified and enforced to the maximum extent permitted by law consistent with the parties'' intent.\n\n13.5 No Partnership; No Fiduciary Duty. This SAFE does not create any partnership, joint venture, agency, or employment relationship between the parties. The Investor is not owed any fiduciary duty by the Company, its directors, officers, or employees solely by reason of this SAFE.\n\n13.6 No Stockholder Rights Until Conversion. This SAFE does not confer on the Investor any rights of a stockholder of the Company (including voting rights, rights to dividends, or rights to receive notices of stockholder meetings) unless and until the SAFE converts into Capital Stock or other equity securities as provided herein.\n\n13.7 Confidentiality; Trade Secrets. The parties acknowledge that any non-public, proprietary information disclosed in connection with this SAFE may be protected under contract and/or the California Uniform Trade Secrets Act (CUTSA), California Civil Code Section 3426 et seq. The Investor agrees to maintain the confidentiality of all non-public information concerning the Company. Any additional confidentiality obligations must be set forth in a separate written agreement.\n\n13.8 Privacy; CCPA Compliance. To the extent the Company collects personal information from the Investor in connection with this SAFE (including identifiers, contact information, and financial information), the Company will use such information for purposes reasonably related to administering the investment relationship, compliance with legal obligations, financing activities, and corporate governance. The Company will not \"sell\" or \"share\" (as those terms are defined under the California Consumer Privacy Act of 2018, as amended by the California Privacy Rights Act of 2020, and implementing regulations) such personal information except as permitted by law. The Investor may exercise applicable privacy rights by contacting the Company at the address set forth herein.\n\n13.9 Counterparts; Electronic Signatures. This SAFE may be executed in one or more counterparts, each of which will be deemed an original and all of which together constitute one and the same instrument. Signatures transmitted electronically (including via PDF, DocuSign, or other commercially reasonable e-signature service) will be deemed original signatures and will be binding and enforceable.\n\n13.10 Entire Agreement. This SAFE constitutes the entire agreement between the parties with respect to the subject matter hereof and supersedes all prior and contemporaneous understandings, agreements, representations, and warranties, whether written or oral, with respect to such subject matter.\n\n13.11 Construction; Headings. Headings are for convenience only and do not affect interpretation. The words \"include,\" \"includes,\" and \"including\" mean \"including without limitation.\" The singular includes the plural and vice versa. \"Or\" is not exclusive.\n\n13.12 Dispute Resolution; Venue. The parties agree that any action or proceeding arising out of or relating to this SAFE will be brought exclusively in the state or federal courts located in {{venue_county}} County, California, and each party irrevocably submits to the personal jurisdiction of such courts and waives any objection to venue therein.\n\n13.13 Expenses. Each party shall bear its own costs and expenses in connection with the negotiation, execution, and delivery of this SAFE.\n\n13.14 Further Assurances. Each party agrees to execute and deliver such additional documents and take such additional actions as may be reasonably necessary to effectuate the purposes of this SAFE.","type":"standard","order":13}]'::jsonb,
  'IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have executed this Simple Agreement for Future Equity as of the Effective Date.

